[Comentario en Core/Business Layer/DataAccess/ReportSystem.cs:2677 por @Copilot]: The PS-69448 diagnostic log here runs for every report generation (including non-ad hoc and non-email requests), which can add significant noise/volume and make the targeted scheduler email investigation harder. Gate this log to just the scheduled ad hoc email path (e.g., `ReportID == ADHOC_REPORT_IDENTIFIER && forEMail`).
[Comentario en Core/Business Layer/DataAccess/ReportSystem.cs:2692 por @Copilot]: `notificationRequest.RecordId` is logged before `SendReports()` persists the notification request via `NotificationSystem.CreateRequest(...)` (which is where `RecordId` is assigned). This means the logged `NotificationRequestID` will typically be 0 and can mislead diagnostics. Log after `SendReports()` (and only when not running under tests) so the ID is populated.
[Comentario en Core/Business Layer/DataAccess/ReportSystem.cs:2676 por @Copilot]: This diagnostic log is currently emitted for *all* ad hoc report generation, including non-email actions (e.g., ad hoc preview/view requests). That can create unnecessary log volume and makes the PS-69448 investigation harder. Gate it to the scheduled email path by requiring `forEMail` as well.
[Comentario en Core/Business Layer/DataAccess/ReportSystem.cs:2695 por @Copilot]: This PS-69448 log in the email path will run for every emailed report (not just ad hoc scheduled reports), which can add significant log noise. Since the PR is targeting diagnostics for the ad hoc report email pipeline, gate this log to `ADHOC_REPORT_IDENTIFIER` (and keep the existing test guard).
[Comentario en Core/Business Layer/DataAccess/ReportSystem.cs:2676 por @Copilot]: This diagnostic log is still emitted for *all* ad hoc report generation, including ad hoc preview/view requests (e.g., `GetReportRequestForAdHocPreviewAsync` builds an ad hoc `ReportRequest` with `Action = View` in this same file). That can create significant log noise and undermines the goal of targeted diagnostics for the scheduled email pipeline. Gate this log to the email path (`forEMail`).
[Comentario en Core/Business Layer/DataAccess/ReportSystem.cs:2695 por @Copilot]: Indentation on this `if` is off (it starts at column 1) which breaks readability and will likely violate the project's formatting rules/.editorconfig. Align it with the surrounding block indentation.
[Comentario en Core/Business Layer/DataAccess/Report/JobHandler.cs:71 por @Copilot]: The warning message leaks an internal field name (`m_RequestedBy`), which is less clear for operational diagnostics than describing the missing context. Consider rewording to a user-focused message (and keep the job identity prefix as you already do on the other warning above).
[Comentario en Core/Business Layer/DataAccess/ReportSystem.cs:2676 por @kcostenbader]: I agree with copilot
